<p><strong>Moving Image Laboratory 2023</strong></p>

<p>From July to September, participants have the opportunity to deepen their knowledge about the history of the moving image and create their own videos, under the guidance of artists with extensive experience in this field of work.</p>

<p>In 2023, Daniel Blaufuks and Andr√© Laranjinha are the invited tutors. At first, and based on his own work, Daniel Blaufuks will be responsible for the theoretical component of the Laboratory, which will serve as a basis for the development of individual projects. The practical orientation will be in charge of Andr√© Laranjinha, with the technical support of Arquip√©lago - Contemporary Arts Center.<br />
<br />
Daniel Blaufuks¬†uses mainly photography and video, presenting his work through books, installations and films. He has a predilection for issues such as the connection between time and space and the intersection between private and public memory.<br />
Andr√© Laranjinha, a visual artist who lives and works in S√£o Miguel, has a degree in Fine Arts from the University of Lisbon and works in cinema, video, visual arts, graphic arts and illustration.</p>

<p>Participation in the Laboratory is free of charge and will take place at Arquip√©lago - Contemporary Arts Center, in Ribeira Grande.</p>

